    &lt;Title&gt;Operation and Critical Care Excellent after care very poor&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I had a triple bypass. I have nothing but praise for the staff in the critical care unit very caring to me and also my loved ones. One to one care absolutely outstanding.
Then moved to the ward. Facilities excellent but not happy with personal care. From the teams I had, if you can't do what the staff ask you to do instantly, they are rude and very pushy to you. 
I didn't open my bowles quick enough, nurse charged in, closed the curtains and said I am going to give you a suppository. I had visitors in the room, no respect for me and my dignity.
My full urinal got knocked over and spilled all over the talbel, this was not cleaned until 2 hours later.
I was not mobile enough to be sent home, but was told, we want to have patients in and out in 5 days.
In my opinion the recovery on the wards is not personal enough to each induvidual need, more conform the box ticking chart.
I have now taken private medical care at home and are recovering much better. &lt;/CommentText&gt;
